<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann. The" authorityName="Wiedemann. The" box="[844,1200,785,809]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compeditus">
<emphasis box="[844,999,785,809]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">P. compeditus</emphasis>
Wiedemann. The
</taxonomicName>
male and the female of the new species can be distinguished as follows: face uniformly rounded medially without a distinct knob, posterior margin of tergite VII of the female with a thickening; the male terminalia are different.
</paragraph>
